First, we need to find the Cartesian product A x B. The Cartesian product of two sets A and B is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is in A and b is in B.

A x B = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of (A x B) x {5}. Let's denote the set (A x B) as C. So, C = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}.

C x {5} = {((1, 3), 5), ((1, 4), 5), ((2, 3), 5), ((2, 4), 5)}

So, (A x B) x {5} = {((1, 3), 5), ((1, 4), 5), ((2, 3), 5), ((2, 4), 5)}.
